  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1107",
  "title": "Proposal: a better documentation",
  "body": "Our current documentation is not good enough. It's mostly an API documentation.\n\nThere's no progressive learning of instantsearch.js. There's no custom use cases explained.\n\nI propose to reorganize it like this:\n- homepage\n- guide\n  - getting started\n  - widgets\n  - templates\n  - url handling #1089 \n  - modular builds\n  - custom widgets\n  - renderers\n  - advanced use cases (targeting multiple indices #1056, jadopado like integration)\n- widgets: one page per widget with API docs, advanced usage and live examples\n- support\n- contact\n- github\n\nIf you have more ideas for the guide please add them, it's a draft.\n\nWe should also take the opportunity to move away from jenkins to middleman.\n",
